<div id="main_content">
	<h2>New Telescope Another Star in UCFÂ’s Rising Astronomy Program</h2>
	
	<p class="article_info">
		
			By Zenaida Gonzalez Kotala
		
		<span class="date">Oct. 4, 2006</span></p>
	
	
	
		<div class="article_img" style="width: 196px;">

			<img alt="Article Main Picture" src="../resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/0/NE876/en_US/060921scopeman.jpg" height="261" width="196"  /> 
			
				<p class="photo_credit">Photo: Jack Schofield</p>
			
			<p>A temporary telescope calls the Robinson Observatory on campus home until it is replaced by a state of the art 20-inch Ritchey-Chretien telescope early next year. The new instrument will give students and professors at UCF more research capabilities.</p>
			
				<p class="note"><a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=0024004105bd60439010c0c76ce2f005f3d">Full Photo</a></p>
			
			
			
			
					
						
						
							
								<h3>Story Images</h3>
								<ul id="story_images">
							
						<li>
						<a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=0024004105bd60439010c0c76ce2f005f3d&amp;img_mode=1&amp;index=0">
							<img width="100" alt="Article Main Picture" src="../resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/0/NE876/en_US/060921scope2.jpg"  />
						</a>
						</li>
						
						
					
			
					
						
						
							
						<li>
						<a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=0024004105bd60439010c0c76ce2f005f3d&amp;img_mode=1&amp;index=1">
							<img width="100" alt="Article Main Picture" src="../resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/0/NE876/en_US/060921scope3.jpg"  />
						</a>
						</li>
						
						
					
			
					
						
						
							
